cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.PF, cs.PL, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
1. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper proposes a parallel version of an algorithm for the Data Distribution Management (DDM) service, which is a core component of High Level Architecture (HLA) used in distributed simulations. The paper also evaluates the performance and scalability of the proposed algorithm on multiprocessors. 
2. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper deals with the problem of identifying intersections between two sets of d-dimensional axis-parallel rectangles, which involves data structures and algorithms for efficient processing. 
3. cs.PF (Performance) - The paper evaluates the performance and scalability of the proposed algorithm on two commodity multicore systems, which is a key aspect of this sub-category. 
4. cs.PL (Programming Languages) - The paper describes the implementation of the proposed algorithm using OpenMP, a popular shared-memory parallel programming model, which is relevant to this sub-category. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with the problem of managing data distribution in a distributed simulation system, which involves systems and control aspects such as synchronization, communication, and resource allocation.
